comments: This is the first time that I had a teacher who is in the wheelchair. In spite of his situation, he is very knowledgeable when it comes to programming. He is very helpful. The only negative I can say is his accent. There are times that I cannot understand what he says. Overall, he is a good teacher.

Viet is the best professor I had met. The reason I can evaluate him because I was a software engineer, briefly: 1. His topic is very useful and critical to programing. 2. He has hands on experiences so he know how to teach instead of talking. 3. Normally if you do not have any background before, this course is difficult.
Couldn\'t understand him due to a heavy Korean accent. He did not follow the syllabus. I learned absolutely nothing from the class.
